^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Very well played. Very interesting hand to bid. Let me say, that although the slam made, it was not particularly good. It turns out 6D is a pretty good contract, because you can afford to lose a diamond. If you look at West's hand, you just have to figure out what to do with the 2 club losers. You can ruff one in dummy, and still only lose 1 diamond, assuming a 3-2 break. So you either have to hope that spades break 3-3 or take the club finesse. All in all, I would put a diamond slam at about 50%, which means if you bid it, you will break even in the long run. 6N on the other hand is not. But, anyway, that validates Marty's point count system.|
