NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now to the play. We already discussed leading pard's suit which beats the hand pretty much off the top, unless Elizabeth is psychic and guesses the stiff King of clubs.However, on the club lead, I think the hand can be made. She can count two clubs, four diamonds, one H and three spades and only needs two spades. So, once the clubs are continued at trick 3, if she just starts on diamonds, she has 9 tricks. Because even if East gets in with the King of spades, she has no hearts to lead back. I think that is the best way to play the hand.|
