^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|There is a treatment some people play known as "equal level conversion doubles"  which works really well on this hand. It basically says if you double, and partner bids the lowest unbid suit, and you correct to the next higher unbid suit, that is not a double and correct. It simply says, you had the 2 higher unbid suits, and no good bid. That works okay on this hand in terms of the bidding, since if you play that, Roberta could correct 3C to 3D, to show a hand with diamonds and spades. That is an advanced treatment, that I do not recommend.|
